    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n               <jats:p>We conjecture that mutual funds with large shares of outstanding bond issues are more inclined to internalize the negative price spillovers of fire sales and thus sell their holdings in those issues, to a lower extent, when they experience redemptions. We provide evidence consistent with this conjecture and further show that ownership concentration limits bonds\u2019 exposures to flow-induced fire sales. We exploit variation in negative spillovers arising from the Fed\u2019s SMCCF to confirm the economic mechanism and explore our findings\u2019 implications for fund performance and fire-sale spillovers to other funds.</jats:p>",
